Israel Stocks: Bio-View, Clal Biotechnology Industries, Sapiens

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-02-20T14:56:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-20/israel-stocks-clal-biotechnology-delta-galil-and-sapiens.html
Israel’s TA-25 Index was little
changed, increasing less than 0.1 percent to 1,335 at the 4:30
p.m. close in Tel Aviv. Investors traded about 1.24 billion
shekels ($344 million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Bio-View Ltd . (BIOV IT) gained to the highest level since
March 2008, increasing 5.9 percent to 2.496 shekels. The maker
of cell-imaging equipment received a 1.7 million-shekel order
for three more scanning systems from a Massachusetts hospital.    Clal Biotechnology Industries Ltd . (CBI IT) rose the most
in almost a week, climbing 2.5 percent to 23.38 shekels. The
company’s 84 percent-owned Andromeda Biotech Ltd. unit completed
recruiting patients for the continuation of a Phase III clinical
trial of its DiaPep277 to treat Type 1 diabetes.  Sapiens International Corp. (SPNS IT) jumped 7.2 percent to
15.34 shekels, the highest since May 2004. The information-
technology company signed a “major” deal with a “leading”
U.S. financial institution to build an operating platform to
manage business decisions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in  Tel Aviv  at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
